{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:05:24.535919+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"from_file silently returns empty AudioSegment when path doesn\\u0026#39;t exist\",\"body\":\"Running into something weird on my CI. When a wav file path is wrong\\n(typo, file not yet copied into the build, etc.), `AudioSegment.from_file`\\nreturns what looks like an empty AudioSegment instead of raising. The\\nfailure shows up much later when I try to slice or export.\\n\\nMinimal reproducer:\\n\\n    from pydub import AudioSegment\\n\\n    # this file does NOT exist on disk\\n    seg = AudioSegment.from_file(\\u0026#34;/tmp/does-not-exist.wav\\u0026#34;)\\n    print(len(seg))  # I expected an exception, got: 0\\n    print(seg.dBFS)  # then: -inf\\n\\nMy read of pydub/utils.py mediainfo_json and audio_segment.py\\nfrom_file is that ffmpeg gets invoked with a missing input and\\nsilently returns nothing useful; the from_file path then proceeds\\nas if it had a valid 0-length segment.\\n\\nIs this intended (treat missing files as 0-length)? Or should\\nfrom_file raise `CouldntDecodeError` (or `FileNotFoundError`) when\\nthe input doesn\\u0026#39;t exist? Happy to send a PR for either direction.\\n\\nffmpeg version: 6.0\\npydub version: 0.25.1\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T11:12:18Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T11:12:22Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQxMToxMjoxOFrPAAAAAQxZP8E=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQxMToxMjoxOFrPAAAAAQxZP8E=\"}}", "id": "lc_35e08e1d-f50a-4013-9f8f-f55a215f6b30"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "a1352f1e-2314-477d-b48a-793a090d3e5a", "tool_call_id": "call_ff38ad10a7a841e7b693ebf2", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
